  <mainDescription>&lt;p>
    A project can be undertaken as a stand-alone set of processes or realised in a multi-project context as part of a
    programme or a project portfolio.
&lt;/p>
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot;>
    This section provides to the reader key information on the concepts of programme which is&amp;nbsp;a collection of projects
    with the same goal and managed in a coordinated way for efficiency purpose. As for a project portfolio, it's collection
    of projects, programmes and activities managed in coordinated way for efficieny purpose and whose complementarity helps
    the organisation achieve its strategic goals.
&lt;/p>
&lt;p align=&quot;justify&quot;>
    Finally, this section contains&amp;nbsp;information on the concept of Agile management, an approach to project management
    centered on flexibility that enables the organisation to successfully adapt to the ever-changing client's needs. The
    following are some Agile management characteristics:&amp;nbsp;Adaptive planning, involving&amp;nbsp;all key project
    stakeholders during the entire project lifecycle, embracing change, incremental developments with short cycles
    (sprints) and minimising project documentation and control
&lt;/p></mainDescription>
